===Phrase===
{{head|en|phrase|head=[[so]] [[be]] [[it]]}}

# {{label|en|idiomatic}} An indication of [[acceptance]], especially of a situation which is not entirely [[favorable]].
#* '''1851''', [[w:Herman Melville|Herman Melville]], ''Moby Dick'', ch. 99:
#*: From storm to storm! '''So be it''', then. Born in throes, 't is fit that man should live in pains and die in pangs! '''So be it''', then! Here's stout stuff for woe to work on. '''So be it''', then.
#* {{quote-news|date=February 22, 2009|title=ABC This Week with George Stephanopoulos|passage=It doesn't matter which party it is. If the people choose one, a Democrat, then '''so be it'''.}}

